The paper deals with algorithms for multi-criteria decision analysis and preference queries, which are common topics in database systems (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also involves the use of algorithms for maximizing the number of expected buyers, which is a problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed algorithms on both synthetic and real data sets, which is a topic in social and information networks (cs.SI).
